\sum_{1}^{\infty}\frac{n}{2^n}
\sum\limits_{0}^{\infty}x^n = \frac{1}{1-x}
x\frac{d}{dx}\frac{1}{1-x} = \sum_{1}^{\infty}nx^{n}
x = 1/2
\frac{d}{dx}\frac{1}{1-x} = \frac{d}{dx}\sum_{0}^{\infty}x^n = \sum_{0}^{\infty}\frac{d}{dx}x^n = \sum_{1}^{\infty}nx^{n-1}
\displaystyle \frac{1}{1-x}=\sum_{n\geqslant 0}x^n
f'(1)
S = \frac{1}{2} + \frac{2}{2^2} + \frac{3}{2^3} + \cdots
 f(x)= \frac{x}{2} + \frac{x^2}{2^2} + \frac{x^3}{2^3} + \cdots = \displaystyle\frac{\frac{x}{2}}{1 - \frac{x}{2}}
